body:
@gaoxuesong, druid can be configured to work with HDP 2.4 (which includes Hadoop 2.7.1 version) 
You will need to follow the steps documented here - 
http://druid.io/docs/latest/operations/other-hadoop.html

@nishantmonu51 @fjy @drcrallen @gianm 

After the latest revisions, this PR now adds support for filtering on all long columns (including __time). 

A new test (LongFilteringTest) has been added that filters on a count aggregator.

@anonymous-shy Adding onto what @gianm says, I would suggest using pull-deps (http://druid.io/docs/latest/operations/pull-deps.html) and looking at the hadoopDependencyCoordinates option in the indexing task, in combination with `mapreduce.job.classpath=true` or `mapreduce.job.user.classpath.first=true`. 

For example, with CDH5.x which uses hadoop 2.6.0:

"hadoopDependencyCoordinates": ["org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-client:2.6.0"]

Here is the unit test https://github.com/kaijianding/druid/blob/testCME/server/src/test/java/io/druid/client/BrokerServerViewTest.java
Please check the testSingleServerAddedSegmentAndRead, it will throw ConcurrentModificationException
@drcrallen
